2542
2543void cvGetOptimalNewCameraMatrix( const CvMat* cameraMatrix, const CvMat* distCoeffs,
2544 CvSize imgSize, double alpha,
2545 CvMat* newCameraMatrix, CvSize newImgSize,
2546 CvRect* validPixROI, int centerPrincipalPoint )
2547{
2548 cv::Rect_<float> inner, outer;
2549 newImgSize = newImgSize.width*newImgSize.height != 0 ? newImgSize : imgSize;
2550
2551 double M[3][3];
2552 CvMat matM = cvMat(3, 3, CV_64F, M);
2553 cvConvert(cameraMatrix, &matM);
2554
2555 if( centerPrincipalPoint )
2556 {
2557 double cx0 = M[0][2];
2558 double cy0 = M[1][2];
2559 double cx = (newImgSize.width-1)*0.5;
2560 double cy = (newImgSize.height-1)*0.5;
2561
2562 icvGetRectangles( cameraMatrix, distCoeffs, 0, cameraMatrix, imgSize, inner, outer );
2563 double s0 = std::max(std::max(std::max((double)cx/(cx0 - inner.x), (double)cy/(cy0 - inner.y)),
2564 (double)cx/(inner.x + inner.width - cx0)),
2565 (double)cy/(inner.y + inner.height - cy0));
2566 double s1 = std::min(std::min(std::min((double)cx/(cx0 - outer.x), (double)cy/(cy0 - outer.y)),
2567 (double)cx/(outer.x + outer.width - cx0)),
2568 (double)cy/(outer.y + outer.height - cy0));
2569 double s = s0*(1 - alpha) + s1*alpha;
2570
2571 M[0][0] *= s;
2572 M[1][1] *= s;
2573 M[0][2] = cx;
2574 M[1][2] = cy;
2575
2576 if( validPixROI )
2577 {
2578 inner = cv::Rect_<float>((float)((inner.x - cx0)*s + cx),
2579 (float)((inner.y - cy0)*s + cy),
2580 (float)(inner.width*s),
2581 (float)(inner.height*s));
2582 cv::Rect r(cvCeil(inner.x), cvCeil(inner.y), cvFloor(inner.width), cvFloor(inner.height));
2583 r &= cv::Rect(0, 0, newImgSize.width, newImgSize.height);
2584 *validPixROI = r;
2585 }
2586 }
2587 else
2588 {
2589 // Get inscribed and circumscribed rectangles in normalized
2590 // (independent of camera matrix) coordinates
2591 icvGetRectangles( cameraMatrix, distCoeffs, 0, 0, imgSize, inner, outer );
2592
2593 // Projection mapping inner rectangle to viewport
2594 double fx0 = (newImgSize.width - 1) / inner.width;
2595 double fy0 = (newImgSize.height - 1) / inner.height;
2596 double cx0 = -fx0 * inner.x;
2597 double cy0 = -fy0 * inner.y;
2598
2599 // Projection mapping outer rectangle to viewport
2600 double fx1 = (newImgSize.width - 1) / outer.width;
2601 double fy1 = (newImgSize.height - 1) / outer.height;
2602 double cx1 = -fx1 * outer.x;
2603 double cy1 = -fy1 * outer.y;
2604
2605 // Interpolate between the two optimal projections
2606 M[0][0] = fx0*(1 - alpha) + fx1*alpha;
2607 M[1][1] = fy0*(1 - alpha) + fy1*alpha;
2608 M[0][2] = cx0*(1 - alpha) + cx1*alpha;
2609 M[1][2] = cy0*(1 - alpha) + cy1*alpha;
2610
2611 if( validPixROI )
2612 {
2613 icvGetRectangles( cameraMatrix, distCoeffs, 0, &matM, imgSize, inner, outer );
2614 cv::Rect r = inner;
2615 r &= cv::Rect(0, 0, newImgSize.width, newImgSize.height);
2616 *validPixROI = r;
2617 }
2618 }
2619
2620 cvConvert(&matM, newCameraMatrix);
2621}

2623
2624CV_IMPL int cvStereoRectifyUncalibrated(
2625 const CvMat* _points1, const CvMat* _points2,
2626 const CvMat* F0, CvSize imgSize,
2627 CvMat* _H1, CvMat* _H2, double threshold )
2628{
2629 Ptr<CvMat> _m1, _m2, _lines1, _lines2;
2630
2631 int i, j, npoints;
2632 double cx, cy;
2633 double u[9], v[9], w[9], f[9], h1[9], h2[9], h0[9], e2[3];
2634 CvMat E2 = cvMat( 3, 1, CV_64F, e2 );
2635 CvMat U = cvMat( 3, 3, CV_64F, u );
2636 CvMat V = cvMat( 3, 3, CV_64F, v );
2637 CvMat W = cvMat( 3, 3, CV_64F, w );
2638 CvMat F = cvMat( 3, 3, CV_64F, f );
2639 CvMat H1 = cvMat( 3, 3, CV_64F, h1 );
2640 CvMat H2 = cvMat( 3, 3, CV_64F, h2 );
2641 CvMat H0 = cvMat( 3, 3, CV_64F, h0 );
2642
2643 CvPoint2D64f* m1;
2644 CvPoint2D64f* m2;
2645 CvPoint3D64f* lines1;
2646 CvPoint3D64f* lines2;
2647
2648 CV_Assert( CV_IS_MAT(_points1) && CV_IS_MAT(_points2) &&
2649 (_points1->rows == 1 || _points1->cols == 1) &&
2650 (_points2->rows == 1 || _points2->cols == 1) &&
2651 CV_ARE_SIZES_EQ(_points1, _points2) );
2652
2653 npoints = _points1->rows * _points1->cols * CV_MAT_CN(_points1->type) / 2;
2654
2655 _m1 = cvCreateMat( _points1->rows, _points1->cols, CV_64FC(CV_MAT_CN(_points1->type)) );
2656 _m2 = cvCreateMat( _points2->rows, _points2->cols, CV_64FC(CV_MAT_CN(_points2->type)) );
2657 _lines1 = cvCreateMat( 1, npoints, CV_64FC3 );
2658 _lines2 = cvCreateMat( 1, npoints, CV_64FC3 );
2659
2660 cvConvert( F0, &F );
2661
2662 cvSVD( (CvMat*)&F, &W, &U, &V, CV_SVD_U_T + CV_SVD_V_T );
2663 W.data.db[8] = 0.;
2664 cvGEMM( &U, &W, 1, 0, 0, &W, CV_GEMM_A_T );
2665 cvMatMul( &W, &V, &F );
2666
2667 cx = cvRound( (imgSize.width-1)*0.5 );
2668 cy = cvRound( (imgSize.height-1)*0.5 );
2669
2670 cvZero( _H1 );
2671 cvZero( _H2 );
2672
2673 cvConvert( _points1, _m1 );
2674 cvConvert( _points2, _m2 );
2675 cvReshape( _m1, _m1, 2, 1 );
2676 cvReshape( _m2, _m2, 2, 1 );
2677
2678 m1 = (CvPoint2D64f*)_m1->data.ptr;
2679 m2 = (CvPoint2D64f*)_m2->data.ptr;
2680 lines1 = (CvPoint3D64f*)_lines1->data.ptr;
2681 lines2 = (CvPoint3D64f*)_lines2->data.ptr;
2682
2683 if( threshold > 0 )
2684 {
2685 cvComputeCorrespondEpilines( _m1, 1, &F, _lines1 );
2686 cvComputeCorrespondEpilines( _m2, 2, &F, _lines2 );
2687
2688 // measure distance from points to the corresponding epilines, mark outliers
2689 for( i = j = 0; i < npoints; i++ )
2690 {
2691 if( fabs(m1[i].x*lines2[i].x +
2692 m1[i].y*lines2[i].y +
2693 lines2[i].z) <= threshold &&
2694 fabs(m2[i].x*lines1[i].x +
2695 m2[i].y*lines1[i].y +
2696 lines1[i].z) <= threshold )
2697 {
2698 if( j < i )
2699 {
2700 m1[j] = m1[i];
2701 m2[j] = m2[i];
2702 }
2703 j++;
2704 }
2705 }
2706
2707 npoints = j;
2708 if( npoints == 0 )
2709 return 0;
2710 }
2711
2712 _m1->cols = _m2->cols = npoints;
2713 memcpy( E2.data.db, U.data.db + 6, sizeof(e2));
2714 cvScale( &E2, &E2, e2[2] > 0 ? 1 : -1 );
2715
2716 double t[] =
2717 {
2718 1, 0, -cx,
2719 0, 1, -cy,
2720 0, 0, 1
2721 };
2722 CvMat T = cvMat(3, 3, CV_64F, t);
2723 cvMatMul( &T, &E2, &E2 );
2724
2725 int mirror = e2[0] < 0;
2726 double d = MAX(sqrt(e2[0]*e2[0] + e2[1]*e2[1]),DBL_EPSILON);
2727 double alpha = e2[0]/d;
2728 double beta = e2[1]/d;
2729 double r[] =
2730 {
2731 alpha, beta, 0,
2732 -beta, alpha, 0,
2733 0, 0, 1
2734 };
2735 CvMat R = cvMat(3, 3, CV_64F, r);
2736 cvMatMul( &R, &T, &T );
2737 cvMatMul( &R, &E2, &E2 );
2738 double invf = fabs(e2[2]) < 1e-6*fabs(e2[0]) ? 0 : -e2[2]/e2[0];
2739 double k[] =
2740 {
2741 1, 0, 0,
2742 0, 1, 0,
2743 invf, 0, 1
2744 };
2745 CvMat K = cvMat(3, 3, CV_64F, k);
2746 cvMatMul( &K, &T, &H2 );
2747 cvMatMul( &K, &E2, &E2 );
2748
2749 double it[] =
2750 {
2751 1, 0, cx,
2752 0, 1, cy,
2753 0, 0, 1
2754 };
2755 CvMat iT = cvMat( 3, 3, CV_64F, it );
2756 cvMatMul( &iT, &H2, &H2 );
2757
2758 memcpy( E2.data.db, U.data.db + 6, sizeof(e2));
2759 cvScale( &E2, &E2, e2[2] > 0 ? 1 : -1 );
2760
2761 double e2_x[] =
2762 {
2763 0, -e2[2], e2[1],
2764 e2[2], 0, -e2[0],
2765 -e2[1], e2[0], 0
2766 };
2767 double e2_111[] =
2768 {
2769 e2[0], e2[0], e2[0],
2770 e2[1], e2[1], e2[1],
2771 e2[2], e2[2], e2[2],
2772 };
2773 CvMat E2_x = cvMat(3, 3, CV_64F, e2_x);
2774 CvMat E2_111 = cvMat(3, 3, CV_64F, e2_111);
2775 cvMatMulAdd(&E2_x, &F, &E2_111, &H0 );
2776 cvMatMul(&H2, &H0, &H0);
2777 CvMat E1=cvMat(3, 1, CV_64F, V.data.db+6);
2778 cvMatMul(&H0, &E1, &E1);
2779
2780 cvPerspectiveTransform( _m1, _m1, &H0 );
2781 cvPerspectiveTransform( _m2, _m2, &H2 );
2782 CvMat A = cvMat( 1, npoints, CV_64FC3, lines1 ), BxBy, B;
2783 double x[3];
2784 CvMat X = cvMat( 3, 1, CV_64F, x );
2785 cvConvertPointsHomogeneous( _m1, &A );
2786 cvReshape( &A, &A, 1, npoints );
2787 cvReshape( _m2, &BxBy, 1, npoints );
2788 cvGetCol( &BxBy, &B, 0 );
2789 cvSolve( &A, &B, &X, CV_SVD );
2790
2791 double ha[] =
2792 {
2793 x[0], x[1], x[2],
2794 0, 1, 0,
2795 0, 0, 1
2796 };
2797 CvMat Ha = cvMat(3, 3, CV_64F, ha);
2798 cvMatMul( &Ha, &H0, &H1 );
2799 cvPerspectiveTransform( _m1, _m1, &Ha );
2800
2801 if( mirror )
2802 {
2803 double mm[] = { -1, 0, cx*2, 0, -1, cy*2, 0, 0, 1 };
2804 CvMat MM = cvMat(3, 3, CV_64F, mm);
2805 cvMatMul( &MM, &H1, &H1 );
2806 cvMatMul( &MM, &H2, &H2 );
2807 }
2808
2809 cvConvert( &H1, _H1 );
2810 cvConvert( &H2, _H2 );
2811
2812 return 1;
2813}

2815
2816void cv::reprojectImageTo3D( InputArray _disparity,
2817 OutputArray __3dImage, InputArray _Qmat,
2818 bool handleMissingValues, int dtype )
2819{
2820 Mat disparity = _disparity.getMat(), Q = _Qmat.getMat();
2821 int stype = disparity.type();
2822
2823 CV_Assert( stype == CV_8UC1 || stype == CV_16SC1 ||
2824 stype == CV_32SC1 || stype == CV_32FC1 );
2825 CV_Assert( Q.size() == Size(4,4) );
2826
2827 if( dtype < 0 )
2828 dtype = CV_32FC3;
2829 else
2830 {
2831 dtype = CV_MAKETYPE(CV_MAT_DEPTH(dtype), 3);
2832 CV_Assert( dtype == CV_16SC3 || dtype == CV_32SC3 || dtype == CV_32FC3 );
2833 }
2834
2835 __3dImage.create(disparity.size(), CV_MAKETYPE(dtype, 3));
2836 Mat _3dImage = __3dImage.getMat();
2837
2838 const double bigZ = 10000.;
2839 double q[4][4];
2840 Mat _Q(4, 4, CV_64F, q);
2841 Q.convertTo(_Q, CV_64F);
2842
2843 int x, cols = disparity.cols;
2844 CV_Assert( cols >= 0 );
2845
2846 vector<float> _sbuf(cols+1), _dbuf(cols*3+1);
2847 float* sbuf = &_sbuf[0], *dbuf = &_dbuf[0];
2848 double minDisparity = FLT_MAX;
2849
2850 // NOTE: here we quietly assume that at least one pixel in the disparity map is not defined.
2851 // and we set the corresponding Z's to some fixed big value.
2852 if( handleMissingValues )
2853 cv::minMaxIdx( disparity, &minDisparity, 0, 0, 0 );
2854
2855 for( int y = 0; y < disparity.rows; y++ )
2856 {
2857 float *sptr = sbuf, *dptr = dbuf;
2858 double qx = q[0][1]*y + q[0][3], qy = q[1][1]*y + q[1][3];
2859 double qz = q[2][1]*y + q[2][3], qw = q[3][1]*y + q[3][3];
2860
2861 if( stype == CV_8UC1 )
2862 {
2863 const uchar* sptr0 = disparity.ptr<uchar>(y);
2864 for( x = 0; x < cols; x++ )
2865 sptr[x] = (float)sptr0[x];
2866 }
2867 else if( stype == CV_16SC1 )
2868 {
2869 const short* sptr0 = disparity.ptr<short>(y);
2870 for( x = 0; x < cols; x++ )
2871 sptr[x] = (float)sptr0[x];
2872 }
2873 else if( stype == CV_32SC1 )
2874 {
2875 const int* sptr0 = disparity.ptr<int>(y);
2876 for( x = 0; x < cols; x++ )
2877 sptr[x] = (float)sptr0[x];
2878 }
2879 else
2880 sptr = (float*)disparity.ptr<float>(y);
2881
2882 if( dtype == CV_32FC3 )
2883 dptr = _3dImage.ptr<float>(y);
2884
2885 for( x = 0; x < cols; x++, qx += q[0][0], qy += q[1][0], qz += q[2][0], qw += q[3][0] )
2886 {
2887 double d = sptr[x];
2888 double iW = 1./(qw + q[3][2]*d);
2889 double X = (qx + q[0][2]*d)*iW;
2890 double Y = (qy + q[1][2]*d)*iW;
2891 double Z = (qz + q[2][2]*d)*iW;
2892 if( fabs(d-minDisparity) <= FLT_EPSILON )
2893 Z = bigZ;
2894
2895 dptr[x*3] = (float)X;
2896 dptr[x*3+1] = (float)Y;
2897 dptr[x*3+2] = (float)Z;
2898 }
2899
2900 if( dtype == CV_16SC3 )
2901 {
2902 short* dptr0 = _3dImage.ptr<short>(y);
2903 for( x = 0; x < cols*3; x++ )
2904 {
2905 int ival = cvRound(dptr[x]);
2906 dptr0[x] = CV_CAST_16S(ival);
2907 }
2908 }
2909 else if( dtype == CV_32SC3 )
2910 {
2911 int* dptr0 = _3dImage.ptr<int>(y);
2912 for( x = 0; x < cols*3; x++ )
2913 {
2914 int ival = cvRound(dptr[x]);
2915 dptr0[x] = ival;
2916 }
2917 }
2918 }
2919}

2922void cvReprojectImageTo3D( const CvArr* disparityImage,
2923 CvArr* _3dImage, const CvMat* matQ,
2924 int handleMissingValues )
2925{
2926 cv::Mat disp = cv::cvarrToMat(disparityImage);
2927 cv::Mat _3dimg = cv::cvarrToMat(_3dImage);
2928 cv::Mat mq = cv::cvarrToMat(matQ);

2934}

2936
2937CV_IMPL void
2938cvRQDecomp3x3( const CvMat *matrixM, CvMat *matrixR, CvMat *matrixQ,
2939 CvMat *matrixQx, CvMat *matrixQy, CvMat *matrixQz,
2940 CvPoint3D64f *eulerAngles)
2941{
2942 double matM[3][3], matR[3][3], matQ[3][3];
2943 CvMat M = cvMat(3, 3, CV_64F, matM);
2944 CvMat R = cvMat(3, 3, CV_64F, matR);
2945 CvMat Q = cvMat(3, 3, CV_64F, matQ);
2946 double z, c, s;
2947
2948 /* Validate parameters. */
2949 CV_Assert( CV_IS_MAT(matrixM) && CV_IS_MAT(matrixR) && CV_IS_MAT(matrixQ) &&
2950 matrixM->cols == 3 && matrixM->rows == 3 &&
2951 CV_ARE_SIZES_EQ(matrixM, matrixR) && CV_ARE_SIZES_EQ(matrixM, matrixQ));
2952
2953 cvConvert(matrixM, &M);
2954
2955 /* Find Givens rotation Q_x for x axis (left multiplication). */
2956 /*
2957 ( 1 0 0 )
2958 Qx = ( 0 c s ), c = m33/sqrt(m32^2 + m33^2), s = m32/sqrt(m32^2 + m33^2)
2959 ( 0 -s c )
2960 */
2961 s = matM[2][1];
2962 c = matM[2][2];
2963 z = 1./sqrt(c * c + s * s + DBL_EPSILON);
2964 c *= z;
2965 s *= z;
2966
2967 double _Qx[3][3] = { {1, 0, 0}, {0, c, s}, {0, -s, c} };
2968 CvMat Qx = cvMat(3, 3, CV_64F, _Qx);
2969
2970 cvMatMul(&M, &Qx, &R);
2971 assert(fabs(matR[2][1]) < FLT_EPSILON);
2972 matR[2][1] = 0;
2973
2974 /* Find Givens rotation for y axis. */
2975 /*
2976 ( c 0 -s )
2977 Qy = ( 0 1 0 ), c = m33/sqrt(m31^2 + m33^2), s = -m31/sqrt(m31^2 + m33^2)
2978 ( s 0 c )
2979 */
2980 s = -matR[2][0];
2981 c = matR[2][2];
2982 z = 1./sqrt(c * c + s * s + DBL_EPSILON);
2983 c *= z;
2984 s *= z;
2985
2986 double _Qy[3][3] = { {c, 0, -s}, {0, 1, 0}, {s, 0, c} };
2987 CvMat Qy = cvMat(3, 3, CV_64F, _Qy);
2988 cvMatMul(&R, &Qy, &M);
2989
2990 assert(fabs(matM[2][0]) < FLT_EPSILON);
2991 matM[2][0] = 0;
2992
2993 /* Find Givens rotation for z axis. */
2994 /*
2995 ( c s 0 )
2996 Qz = (-s c 0 ), c = m22/sqrt(m21^2 + m22^2), s = m21/sqrt(m21^2 + m22^2)
2997 ( 0 0 1 )
2998 */
2999
3000 s = matM[1][0];
3001 c = matM[1][1];
3002 z = 1./sqrt(c * c + s * s + DBL_EPSILON);
3003 c *= z;
3004 s *= z;
3005
3006 double _Qz[3][3] = { {c, s, 0}, {-s, c, 0}, {0, 0, 1} };
3007 CvMat Qz = cvMat(3, 3, CV_64F, _Qz);
3008
3009 cvMatMul(&M, &Qz, &R);
3010 assert(fabs(matR[1][0]) < FLT_EPSILON);
3011 matR[1][0] = 0;
3012
3013 // Solve the decomposition ambiguity.
3014 // Diagonal entries of R, except the last one, shall be positive.
3015 // Further rotate R by 180 degree if necessary
3016 if( matR[0][0] < 0 )
3017 {
3018 if( matR[1][1] < 0 )
3019 {
3020 // rotate around z for 180 degree, i.e. a rotation matrix of
3021 // [-1, 0, 0],
3022 // [ 0, -1, 0],
3023 // [ 0, 0, 1]
3024 matR[0][0] *= -1;
3025 matR[0][1] *= -1;
3026 matR[1][1] *= -1;
3027
3028 _Qz[0][0] *= -1;
3029 _Qz[0][1] *= -1;
3030 _Qz[1][0] *= -1;
3031 _Qz[1][1] *= -1;
3032 }
3033 else
3034 {
3035 // rotate around y for 180 degree, i.e. a rotation matrix of
3036 // [-1, 0, 0],
3037 // [ 0, 1, 0],
3038 // [ 0, 0, -1]
3039 matR[0][0] *= -1;
3040 matR[0][2] *= -1;
3041 matR[1][2] *= -1;
3042 matR[2][2] *= -1;
3043
3044 cvTranspose( &Qz, &Qz );
3045
3046 _Qy[0][0] *= -1;
3047 _Qy[0][2] *= -1;
3048 _Qy[2][0] *= -1;
3049 _Qy[2][2] *= -1;
3050 }
3051 }
3052 else if( matR[1][1] < 0 )
3053 {
3054 // ??? for some reason, we never get here ???
3055
3056 // rotate around x for 180 degree, i.e. a rotation matrix of
3057 // [ 1, 0, 0],
3058 // [ 0, -1, 0],
3059 // [ 0, 0, -1]
3060 matR[0][1] *= -1;
3061 matR[0][2] *= -1;
3062 matR[1][1] *= -1;
3063 matR[1][2] *= -1;
3064 matR[2][2] *= -1;
3065
3066 cvTranspose( &Qz, &Qz );
3067 cvTranspose( &Qy, &Qy );
3068
3069 _Qx[1][1] *= -1;
3070 _Qx[1][2] *= -1;
3071 _Qx[2][1] *= -1;
3072 _Qx[2][2] *= -1;
3073 }
3074
3075 // calculate the euler angle
3076 if( eulerAngles )
3077 {
3078 eulerAngles->x = acos(_Qx[1][1]) * (_Qx[1][2] >= 0 ? 1 : -1) * (180.0 / CV_PI);
3079 eulerAngles->y = acos(_Qy[0][0]) * (_Qy[2][0] >= 0 ? 1 : -1) * (180.0 / CV_PI);
3080 eulerAngles->z = acos(_Qz[0][0]) * (_Qz[0][1] >= 0 ? 1 : -1) * (180.0 / CV_PI);
3081 }
3082
3083 /* Calulate orthogonal matrix. */
3084 /*
3085 Q = QzT * QyT * QxT
3086 */
3087 cvGEMM( &Qz, &Qy, 1, 0, 0, &M, CV_GEMM_A_T + CV_GEMM_B_T );
3088 cvGEMM( &M, &Qx, 1, 0, 0, &Q, CV_GEMM_B_T );
3089
3090 /* Save R and Q matrices. */
3091 cvConvert( &R, matrixR );
3092 cvConvert( &Q, matrixQ );
3093
3094 if( matrixQx )
3095 cvConvert(&Qx, matrixQx);
3096 if( matrixQy )
3097 cvConvert(&Qy, matrixQy);
3098 if( matrixQz )
3099 cvConvert(&Qz, matrixQz);
3100}
3101
3102
3103CV_IMPL void
3104cvDecomposeProjectionMatrix( const CvMat *projMatr, CvMat *calibMatr,
3105 CvMat *rotMatr, CvMat *posVect,
3106 CvMat *rotMatrX, CvMat *rotMatrY,
3107 CvMat *rotMatrZ, CvPoint3D64f *eulerAngles)
3108{
3109 double tmpProjMatrData[16], tmpMatrixDData[16], tmpMatrixVData[16];
3110 CvMat tmpProjMatr = cvMat(4, 4, CV_64F, tmpProjMatrData);
3111 CvMat tmpMatrixD = cvMat(4, 4, CV_64F, tmpMatrixDData);
3112 CvMat tmpMatrixV = cvMat(4, 4, CV_64F, tmpMatrixVData);
3113 CvMat tmpMatrixM;
3114
3115 /* Validate parameters. */
3116 if(projMatr == 0 || calibMatr == 0 || rotMatr == 0 || posVect == 0)
3117 CV_Error(CV_StsNullPtr, "Some of parameters is a NULL pointer!");
3118
3119 if(!CV_IS_MAT(projMatr) || !CV_IS_MAT(calibMatr) || !CV_IS_MAT(rotMatr) || !CV_IS_MAT(posVect))
3120 CV_Error(CV_StsUnsupportedFormat, "Input parameters must be a matrices!");
3121
3122 if(projMatr->cols != 4 || projMatr->rows != 3)
3123 CV_Error(CV_StsUnmatchedSizes, "Size of projection matrix must be 3x4!");
3124
3125 if(calibMatr->cols != 3 || calibMatr->rows != 3 || rotMatr->cols != 3 || rotMatr->rows != 3)
3126 CV_Error(CV_StsUnmatchedSizes, "Size of calibration and rotation matrices must be 3x3!");
3127
3128 if(posVect->cols != 1 || posVect->rows != 4)
3129 CV_Error(CV_StsUnmatchedSizes, "Size of position vector must be 4x1!");
3130
3131 /* Compute position vector. */
3132 cvSetZero(&tmpProjMatr); // Add zero row to make matrix square.
3133 int i, k;
3134 for(i = 0; i < 3; i++)
3135 for(k = 0; k < 4; k++)
3136 cvmSet(&tmpProjMatr, i, k, cvmGet(projMatr, i, k));
3137
3138 cvSVD(&tmpProjMatr, &tmpMatrixD, NULL, &tmpMatrixV, CV_SVD_MODIFY_A + CV_SVD_V_T);
3139
3140 /* Save position vector. */
3141 for(i = 0; i < 4; i++)
3142 cvmSet(posVect, i, 0, cvmGet(&tmpMatrixV, 3, i)); // Solution is last row of V.
3143
3144 /* Compute calibration and rotation matrices via RQ decomposition. */
3145 cvGetCols(projMatr, &tmpMatrixM, 0, 3); // M is first square matrix of P.
3146
3147 CV_Assert(cvDet(&tmpMatrixM) != 0.0); // So far only finite cameras could be decomposed, so M has to be nonsingular [det(M) != 0].
3148
3149 cvRQDecomp3x3(&tmpMatrixM, calibMatr, rotMatr, rotMatrX, rotMatrY, rotMatrZ, eulerAngles);
3150}

3681static void adjust3rdMatrix(InputArrayOfArrays _imgpt1_0,
3682 InputArrayOfArrays _imgpt3_0,
3683 const Mat& cameraMatrix1, const Mat& distCoeffs1,
3684 const Mat& cameraMatrix3, const Mat& distCoeffs3,
3685 const Mat& R1, const Mat& R3, const Mat& P1, Mat& P3 )
3686{
3687 size_t n1 = _imgpt1_0.total(), n3 = _imgpt3_0.total();
3688 vector<Point2f> imgpt1, imgpt3;
3689
3690 for( int i = 0; i < (int)std::min(n1, n3); i++ )
3691 {
3692 Mat pt1 = _imgpt1_0.getMat(i), pt3 = _imgpt3_0.getMat(i);
3693 int ni1 = pt1.checkVector(2, CV_32F), ni3 = pt3.checkVector(2, CV_32F);
3694 CV_Assert( ni1 > 0 && ni1 == ni3 );
3695 const Point2f* pt1data = pt1.ptr<Point2f>();
3696 const Point2f* pt3data = pt3.ptr<Point2f>();
3697 std::copy(pt1data, pt1data + ni1, std::back_inserter(imgpt1));
3698 std::copy(pt3data, pt3data + ni3, std::back_inserter(imgpt3));
3699 }
3700
3701 undistortPoints(imgpt1, imgpt1, cameraMatrix1, distCoeffs1, R1, P1);
3702 undistortPoints(imgpt3, imgpt3, cameraMatrix3, distCoeffs3, R3, P3);
3703
3704 double y1_ = 0, y2_ = 0, y1y1_ = 0, y1y2_ = 0;
3705 size_t n = imgpt1.size();
3706
3707 for( size_t i = 0; i < n; i++ )
3708 {
3709 double y1 = imgpt3[i].y, y2 = imgpt1[i].y;
3710
3711 y1_ += y1; y2_ += y2;
3712 y1y1_ += y1*y1; y1y2_ += y1*y2;
3713 }
3714
3715 y1_ /= n;
3716 y2_ /= n;
3717 y1y1_ /= n;
3718 y1y2_ /= n;
3719
3720 double a = (y1y2_ - y1_*y2_)/(y1y1_ - y1_*y1_);
3721 double b = y2_ - a*y1_;
3722
3723 P3.at<double>(0,0) *= a;
3724 P3.at<double>(1,1) *= a;
3725 P3.at<double>(0,2) = P3.at<double>(0,2)*a;
3726 P3.at<double>(1,2) = P3.at<double>(1,2)*a + b;
3727 P3.at<double>(0,3) *= a;
3728 P3.at<double>(1,3) *= a;
3729}
3730
3731}

3733float cv::rectify3Collinear( InputArray _cameraMatrix1, InputArray _distCoeffs1,
3734 InputArray _cameraMatrix2, InputArray _distCoeffs2,
3735 InputArray _cameraMatrix3, InputArray _distCoeffs3,
3736 InputArrayOfArrays _imgpt1,
3737 InputArrayOfArrays _imgpt3,
3738 Size imageSize, InputArray _Rmat12, InputArray _Tmat12,
3739 InputArray _Rmat13, InputArray _Tmat13,
3740 OutputArray _Rmat1, OutputArray _Rmat2, OutputArray _Rmat3,
3741 OutputArray _Pmat1, OutputArray _Pmat2, OutputArray _Pmat3,
3742 OutputArray _Qmat,
3743 double alpha, Size newImgSize,
3744 Rect* roi1, Rect* roi2, int flags )
3745{
3746 // first, rectify the 1-2 stereo pair
3747 stereoRectify( _cameraMatrix1, _distCoeffs1, _cameraMatrix2, _distCoeffs2,
3748 imageSize, _Rmat12, _Tmat12, _Rmat1, _Rmat2, _Pmat1, _Pmat2, _Qmat,
3749 flags, alpha, newImgSize, roi1, roi2 );
3750
3751 Mat R12 = _Rmat12.getMat(), R13 = _Rmat13.getMat(), T12 = _Tmat12.getMat(), T13 = _Tmat13.getMat();
3752
3753 _Rmat3.create(3, 3, CV_64F);
3754 _Pmat3.create(3, 4, CV_64F);
3755
3756 Mat P1 = _Pmat1.getMat(), P2 = _Pmat2.getMat();
3757 Mat R3 = _Rmat3.getMat(), P3 = _Pmat3.getMat();
3758
3759 // recompute rectification transforms for cameras 1 & 2.
3760 Mat om, r_r, r_r13;
3761
3762 if( R13.size() != Size(3,3) )
3763 Rodrigues(R13, r_r13);
3764 else
3765 R13.copyTo(r_r13);
3766
3767 if( R12.size() == Size(3,3) )
3768 Rodrigues(R12, om);
3769 else
3770 R12.copyTo(om);
3771
3772 om *= -0.5;
3773 Rodrigues(om, r_r); // rotate cameras to same orientation by averaging
3774 Mat_<double> t12 = r_r * T12;
3775
3776 int idx = fabs(t12(0,0)) > fabs(t12(1,0)) ? 0 : 1;
3777 double c = t12(idx,0), nt = norm(t12, CV_L2);
3778 Mat_<double> uu = Mat_<double>::zeros(3,1);
3779 uu(idx, 0) = c > 0 ? 1 : -1;
3780
3781 // calculate global Z rotation
3782 Mat_<double> ww = t12.cross(uu), wR;
3783 double nw = norm(ww, CV_L2);
3784 ww *= acos(fabs(c)/nt)/nw;
3785 Rodrigues(ww, wR);
3786
3787 // now rotate camera 3 to make its optical axis parallel to cameras 1 and 2.
3788 R3 = wR*r_r.t()*r_r13.t();
3789 Mat_<double> t13 = R3 * T13;
3790
3791 P2.copyTo(P3);
3792 Mat t = P3.col(3);
3793 t13.copyTo(t);
3794 P3.at<double>(0,3) *= P3.at<double>(0,0);
3795 P3.at<double>(1,3) *= P3.at<double>(1,1);
3796
3797 if( !_imgpt1.empty() && _imgpt3.empty() )
3798 adjust3rdMatrix(_imgpt1, _imgpt3, _cameraMatrix1.getMat(), _distCoeffs1.getMat(),
3799 _cameraMatrix3.getMat(), _distCoeffs3.getMat(), _Rmat1.getMat(), R3, P1, P3);
3800
3801 return (float)((P3.at<double>(idx,3)/P3.at<double>(idx,idx))/
3802 (P2.at<double>(idx,3)/P2.at<double>(idx,idx)));
3803}
